comment.shortText:
A Map with additional utility methods. This is used throughout discord.js rather than Arrays for anything that has
an ID, for significantly improved performance and ease-of-use.

tags.text: {number} size - The amount of elements in this collection.

comment.shortText: Returns an iterable of entries in the map.

Creates an ordered array of the values of this collection, and caches it internally. The array will only be
reconstructed if an item is added to or removed from the collection, or if you change the length of the array
itself. If you don't want this caching behavior, use `[...collection.values()]` or
`Array.from(collection.values())` instead.

Identical to [Map.clear()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Map/clear).
Removes all elements from the collection.
Creates an identical shallow copy of this collection.
Combines this collection with others into a new collection. None of the source collections are modified.

comment.text: Collections to merge

comment.shortText:
Identical to [Map.delete()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Map/delete).
Deletes an element from the collection.
comment.returns: `true` if the element was removed, `false` if the element does not exist.

comment.text: The key to delete from the collection

comment.shortText: The difference method returns a new structure containing items where the key is present in one of the original structures but not the other.

comment.shortText:
Identical to
[Map.forEach()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Map/forEach),
but returns the collection instead of undefined.

comment.text: Function to execute for each element

comment.shortText: Returns an iterable of key, value pairs for every entry in the map.

Checks if this collection shares identical items with another.
This is different to checking for equality using equal-signs, because
the collections may be different objects, but contain the same data.
comment.returns: Whether the collections have identical contents

comment.text: Collection to compare with

comment.shortText:
Checks if all items passes a test. Identical in behavior to
[Array.every()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/every).

comment.text: Function used to test (should return a boolean)

comment.shortText:
Identical to
[Array.filter()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/filter),
but returns a Collection instead of an Array.

comment.text: The function to test with (should return boolean)

comment.shortText:
Searches for a single item where the given function returns a truthy value. This behaves like
[Array.find()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/find).
<warn>All collections used in Discord.js are mapped using their `id` property, and if you want to find by id you
should use the `get` method. See
[MDN](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Map/get) for details.</warn>

comment.text: The function to test with (should return boolean)

comment.shortText:
Searches for the key of a single item where the given function returns a truthy value. This behaves like
[Array.findIndex()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/findIndex),
but returns the key rather than the positional index.

comment.text: The function to test with (should return boolean)

comment.shortText: Obtains the first value(s) in this collection.
comment.returns:
A single value if no amount is provided or an array of values, starting from the end if
amount is negative

comment.shortText: Obtains the first key(s) in this collection.
comment.returns:
A single key if no amount is provided or an array of keys, starting from the end if
amount is negative

comment.shortText:
Maps each item into a Collection, then joins the results into a single Collection. Identical in behavior to
[Array.flatMap()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/flatMap).

comment.text: Function that produces a new Collection

comment.shortText:
Identical to [Map.get()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Map/get).
Gets an element with the specified key, and returns its value, or `undefined` if the element does not exist.

comment.text: The key to get from this collection

comment.shortText:
Identical to [Map.has()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Map/has).
Checks if an element exists in the collection.
comment.returns: `true` if the element exists, `false` if it does not exist.

comment.text: The key of the element to check for

comment.shortText: The intersect method returns a new structure containing items where the keys are present in both original structures.

comment.text: The other Collection to filter against

comment.shortText:
Creates an ordered array of the keys of this collection, and caches it internally. The array will only be
reconstructed if an item is added to or removed from the collection, or if you change the length of the array
itself. If you don't want this caching behavior, use `[...collection.keys()]` or
`Array.from(collection.keys())` instead.
Returns an iterable of keys in the map

Obtains the last value(s) in this collection. This relies on {@link Collection#array}, and thus the caching
mechanism applies here as well.
comment.returns:
A single value if no amount is provided or an array of values, starting from the start if
amount is negative

comment.shortText:
Obtains the last key(s) in this collection. This relies on {@link Collection#keyArray}, and thus the caching
mechanism applies here as well.
comment.returns:
A single key if no amount is provided or an array of keys, starting from the start if
amount is negative

comment.shortText:
Maps each item to another value into an array. Identical in behavior to
[Array.map()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/map).

comment.text: Function that produces an element of the new array, taking three arguments

comment.shortText:
Maps each item to another value into a collection. Identical in behavior to
[Array.map()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/map).

comment.text: Function that produces an element of the new collection, taking three arguments

comment.shortText:
Partitions the collection into two collections where the first collection
contains the items that passed and the second contains the items that failed.

comment.text: Function used to test (should return a boolean)

comment.shortText:
Obtains unique random value(s) from this collection. This relies on {@link Collection#array}, and thus the caching
mechanism applies here as well.
comment.returns: A single value if no amount is provided or an array of values

comment.shortText:
Obtains unique random key(s) from this collection. This relies on {@link Collection#keyArray}, and thus the caching
mechanism applies here as well.
comment.returns: A single key if no amount is provided or an array

comment.shortText:
Applies a function to produce a single value. Identical in behavior to
[Array.reduce()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/reduce).

comment.text:
Function used to reduce, taking four arguments; `accumulator`, `currentValue`, `currentKey`,
and `collection`

comment.shortText:
Identical to [Map.set()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Map/set).
Sets a new element in the collection with the specified key and value.

comment.text: The key of the element to add
The value of the element to add

Checks if there exists an item that passes a test. Identical in behavior to

comment.shortText:
The sort method sorts the items of a collection in place and returns it.
The sort is not necessarily stable in Node 10 or older.
The default sort order is according to string Unicode code points.

The sorted method sorts the items of a collection and returns it.
The sort is not necessarily stable in Node 10 or older.
The default sort order is according to string Unicode code points.
Removes items that satisfy the provided filter function.
